Increased from 15,000 to 25,000.

87
00:04:38.880 --> 00:04:39.120
So-

88
00:04:39.240 --> 00:04:39.360
Okay

89
00:04:39.540 --> 00:04:43.220
... in essence, you should only need an administrator if you have less than

90
00:04:43.230 --> 00:04:45.160
$25,000 worth of assets.

91
00:04:45.350 --> 00:04:46.700
Yes. Or income.

92
00:04:46.780 --> 00:04:49.120
Or income. Sorry, yes, and/or income.

93
00:04:49.570 --> 00:04:49.570
38,000.

94
00:04:49.570 --> 00:04:53.340
And the other thing you haven't mentioned that you might want to identify, which

95
00:04:53.380 --> 00:04:57.230
is critical, is that previously there was a fund to

96
00:04:57.360 --> 00:04:59.460
pay the fees, and that was removed, wasn't it?

97
00:04:59.540 --> 00:05:00.140
That's correct.

98
00:05:00.370 --> 00:05:00.370
Okay. All right.

99
00:05:00.400 --> 00:05:01.800
So I was just getting into that now.

100
00:05:01.810 --> 00:05:02.719
Just close. Yeah. Cool.

101
00:05:02.760 --> 00:05:03.120
Yeah.

102
00:05:04.360 --> 00:05:08.310
So in principle, raising the thresholds means that less

103
00:05:08.310 --> 00:05:11.140
